description: This one is a professionally built street and strip car.  Powered by a muscled up 440 big block channeled through a 727 Torqueflite trans with a Hurst Pro Matic 2 shifter and delivered to the road via the 3.90 Post Rear End, you can either curl or straighten your hair with this one.  The strip side of the conversion includes tide frame rails, a stiffer suspension to handle the torque, there is no frivolous radio in the dash, a full set of custom installed Stuart Warner gauges and tach are added along with a fire extinguisher mounted to the tunnel, there are leather form fitting articulating leather Recaro front bucket seats that give you comfort and support, while the back seat has been removed for weight loss.  There are some comfort creatures added for the street side of things including power steering and brakes and a custom built cup holder and console between the seats. The hood has twin scoops and pins added for looks and function. The black paint is mirror smooth and the interior is all new.  Era correct polished Cragar SS wheels with black wall radials finish off the look. While the performance tuned dual exhaust shouts an early warning to anyone that might think this is just a pretty car.

description: The original Plymouth Duster is a semi-fastback two-door coupe version of the compact-sized Plymouth Valiant automobile that was marketed by Plymouth in the U.S. from 1970 to 1976 model years. As the Barracuda grew in dimension, the hole it left in Plymouth lineup was filled by the Duster. The Duster produced a sporty, inexpensive compact that was a lot of bang for the buck. The design is known for its semi-fastback roof and (starting in 1973) the taillights that were mounted from the outside and trimmed in chrome.

GR Auto Gallery is pleased to present this 1972 Plymouth Duster for consideration. This vehicle is powered by a 340ci V8 engine that runs like a top and turns right over as it should. It is paired to an original 3-speed automatic transmission that shifts smoothly and is strong in every gear. The exterior orange paint has held up extremely well over the years and looks phenomenal after receiving a full vehicle detail. The orange is matched with a white vinyl interior that looks great and appears to have been maintained very well; there are a few pieces of trim missing, but no major damage, rips or issues throughout. The owner of this vehicle has kept every piece of documentation on it that has crossed the path, a full binder of receipts and miscellaneous documentation will come along with the car. Please call or email us today for more information on this 1972 Plymouth Duster.
To see over 80 photos of this car, including under carriage please visit our website www.grautogallery.com

description: 1956 Plymouth Belvedere Two Door Hardtop

Plymouth's Belvedere was the top of the line series in 1954 through 1958. This example is a striking automobile in just beautiful condition inside and out. This car was originally out of California. We have a slew of original documentation along with the original set of steel wheels & factory hubcaps. The 38,511 miles are original to the car according to the original documents. This is a collector quality '56 Plymouth Belvedere. Enjoy the presentation and feel free to contact Dave at 214-213-7072 or Maris at 214-616-2317 with any questions.
We have documents showing the 2 original owners and that the car was a California car for many years before coming to Texas.
FEATURES & SPECIFICATIONS INCLUDE :
277 Cubic Inch "HyFire" V8 Engine
Powerflite Pushbutton 2-Speed Automatic Transmission
Real Wire Wheels & Wide Whitewall Tires - Original Steel Wheels & Beauty Caps Included
Original Documentation, Registration, Vintage Advertising, & more
Factory Power Steering
AM Factory Radio
Black Base/Clearcoat Exterior
Pink & Black Original Type Interior
Collector Quality Car - Dave at 214-213-7072 or Maris at 214-616-2317

Under the hood is the previously rebuilt 277 cubic inch HyFire Plymouth V8. This power plant is paired with the factory Powerflite 2-speed automatic transmission.
